Diagnosis.
The new species can be diagnosed by the following set of characters: (
1
) SVL 
26.2–30.2 mm
in males; (
2
) tympanic membrane absent; (
3
) snout protruding in profile; (
4
) vocal sac single, subgular, moderately developed, extending to the middle of the pectoral region, with longitudinal folds; (
5
) canthal white line present; (
6
) dorsolateral white line from the eye to sacral region; (
7
) dorsolateral black line from the tip of snout extending beyond the eye to gradually disappearing up to the flanks; (
8
) slender forearm in males; (
9
